Package: babinium-play
Version: 1.2.1
Section: video
Priority: optional
Architecture: all
Maintainer: babinium <babinium@users.noreply.github.com>
Depends: python3, python3-tk, python3-pil, python3-pil.imagetk, mpv, ca-certificates
Homepage: https://github.com/babinium/Babinium-play
Description: Lightweight YouTube player for low-resource Linux systems
 Babinium Play is a minimal YouTube music and video player designed for
 lightweight Debian-based distributions such as antiX, Debian, Ubuntu,
 Zorin OS Lite, and Linux Mint.
 .
 It uses a small Tkinter interface and mpv for playback. A recent yt-dlp
 library is bundled as pure Python code so playback keeps working on
 stable or lightweight distributions that ship older yt-dlp packages.
